This paper deals with object pose estimation using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper focuses on autonomous robot manipulation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with the estimation of 3D orientation from 2D images.
